ee on civil FCFS, then angry FFA will be the end result of trying to fix this broken reservations system.<br>
<br>
Eoral, under the current reservations system, planes raids are only great fun if you have the time to sit in front of your computer for 8-10 hours at a time in the wee hours of the morning.  And there will always be a huge number of people who will fight change, simply because it would be contrary to their own personal comfort level.. even when it's time has come, and when you step back to really look at the situation logically, it's obviously for the better.<br>
<br>
Ahzag, I feel it is you who's projections are flawed.  You speak as though the market is *already* flooded; as though everyone who is interested in playing these types of games is already involved in them, and in particular, in EQ.  I beg to differ; I feel the market will continue to grow and prosper for some time, especially with a wider range of choices available. I suppose that just because AOL sucks compared to the real ISP's out there, you'd also figure they would have gone out of business 6 years ago, too?  Didn't we all *grins*?   I also have to disagree with your assessment of the new games coming out; true, Anarchy (and Shadowbane, for that matter) seem interested in attracting the more &quot;juvenile&quot; player base, but DAoC is most certainly not what I'd call a &quot;power gamers&quot; choice.  Quite the contrary: I feel the Role Players will flock to Dark Age of Camelot, while the power gamers will instead choose to remain with EQ, where it's actually quite easy to progress upwards in level, due to the structure of the game itself as well as the many web-published &quot;how to&quot; guides that are readily available now.  Not to mention all the sub-20th level people running around with high-level gear these days.<br>
<br>
Hallwin, is there posted anywhere a complete listing of the Guilds who were represented at this so-called &quot;Meeting of the Minds?&quot;  I'd be curious to compare that to a listing of active Guilds on the server.<br>
<br>
Nadia, 500 votes?  That's an impressive number.. it's almost a huge whopping 25% of the server population on a weekday evening, during peak time.  Now, if you figure that only half the people who play, even &quot;regularly&quot;, make it on every other night... that would make the 500 votes a reflection of approximately 12.5% of the populace of Brell. And this does not count ANY of the &quot;casual gamers&quot;.  No, not a bad turnout, but I'm afraid my initial claim that only a small percentage of Brell's population bothers to come here is only reinforced by these figures, and not the opposite.  500 is how many came when there was an active, server-wide effort to participate in this vote.  500 is not the number who regularly visit these boards, where all these so-called Policies are put into place for the rest of us.<br>
<br>
Thank you all for discussing this in a civil manner, minus the flames.  My opinion stands.. but I'm nobody in particular, so don't worry yourselves about it *smiles*.<br>
<br>
